title: 2013 - The Year In Christian Music (Bundle 41)
description:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
2013 - THE YEAR IN CHRISTIAN MUSIC
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Let me start off by saying that this bundle is absolutely packed and stacked.  With 46 releases, you're sure to find something within that brings joy to your heart this coming weekend.  Of course there are 20 singles.  Yes, 20!  That's way more than usual.  What can I say?  I stumbled upon a stash of them earlier this week.  And with Christmas just around the corner, there's also lots and lots of holiday music also included within.

If I attempt to break this 41st bundle down into genres, for those interested, it would go something like this...

There would be six Rock to choose from including Aaron Sprinkle, Casting Crowns, Jesse Sprinkle, Mark Tiddy, The Neverclaim, and Steven Curtis Chapman.  We've got two categorized under R&B including Aaron Thomas, and Jennifer Hudson.  If you're looking for Singer-Songwriter, then consider Amos Lee, Gungor, Jamestown Story, Michael Boggs, Mitch Langley, and Repent.  If you're looking for Hip-Hop/Rap rap today, your options are Bakah, Eshon Burgundy, Fog, Frobeats, Jeffrey Alan, and Luke.  As I said earlier, this thing is jammed to the max with Christmas music today including Brandon Heath, Britt Nicole, Building 429, Colton Dixon, Matt Maher, Meredith Andrews, Rhett Walker Band, Sanctus Real, Sidewalk Prophets, Tenth Avenue North, and the latest WoW Christmas release.  Maybe you're looking Pop music?  How about Brett Blondell, Gabi DiPace, Jon McLaughlin, Kari Jobe, Keila Garza, and Mikeschair.  Contemporary music?  Then be sure to check out Dara Maclean, Ohio Avenue, and Shane Harper.  I've even got a rare Reggae release (given that I don't often find much Christian Reggae) today from Hyer Dan.  There are two Praise & Worship albums to choose from including The Relentless Project, and Russell Fragar.  And finally, if Metal/Hardcore is your thing, then you're going to want to get a copy of Seraphim for your collection.

Bundle 41 includes the following 46 releases, bringing out total shared for the year up to 1,140 titles...
